    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - FRONT COVER - REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to the appropriate manual sections prior to front cover removal and remove the
                following components:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Vibration damper</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Oil pump assembly</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Water pump to thermostat housing hose</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Water pump and pulley</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Oil pan</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Oil pickup tube</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fuel injection pump</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fuel injection lines (high pressure)</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fuel return tube at injection pump</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fuel filter to supply pump tube</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Throttle return springs</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Aneroid tube</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the injection pump drive gear access cover as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove six fasteners which secure the access cover (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150808">8.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the access cover and gasket. Discard gasket.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The current model year engines incorporate a simplified injection pump access cover as
                            part of the revised accessory drive. Refer to Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150809">8.9</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4150808" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11796" filename="../figcg1/cg11796.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.8. Injection Pump Access Cover Identification.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150809" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11965" filename="../figcg1/cg11965.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.9. Injection Pump Access Cover) (Engine S/N Below 532981).</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Access Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Cover Gasket</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Tach Drive Adapter</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Seal Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">5. Crab Bracket</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">6. Cup Plug</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">7. Dowel Pins</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Engines equipped with either a mechanical or electronic tachometer may be removed while
                            attached to the access cover.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk document="e415_HL4151103.xml" xrefid="hl4151103">Remove the injection pump drive gear and the
                    injection pump.
                </hotlnk>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>PRIOR TO REMOVING THE INJECTION PUMP, FOLLOW THE
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4151103.xml" xrefid="hl4151103">INJECTION PUMP TO ENGINE TIMING
                            PROCEDURE
                        </hotlnk>
                        TO FACILITATE REASSEMBLY.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front cover as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">On engines equipped with a gear driven pump remove the two nuts which secure the power
                    steering pump or cover at the rear of the front cover and front plate. Remove the cover and discard
                    the gasket (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_172.xml" xrefid="ef4150810">8.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Rotate engine to vertical position, on the engine stand. (Front cover facing up.) This
                            allows retention of the hardware in the cover and minimizes the chances of crankshaft
                            damage.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen (but do not remove) all the front cover mounting bolts which secure front cover
                    to crankcase (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_172.xml" xrefid="ef4150811">8.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lift the front cover (with hardware) from the crankcase and set aside.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove front cover gasket and discard.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
